"Among the criticisms of Kettlewell's original predation experiments (and these were first raised by Kettlewell, himself) is that the numbers of moths he released on trees created artificially high densities, and that the moths were put onto the trunks of trees which may not be where they actually pass the day exposed to predators. "[and in fact, at best only a miniscule and negligible fraction of the total wild moth population has ever been observed to do this.--ww]